6 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
7 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
8 Article – Labor and Employment
9 8–101.
10 (a) In this title the following words have the meanings indicated.
11 (b) “Base period” means:
12 (1) the first 4 of the last 5 completed calendar quarters immediately
13 preceding the start of the benefit year; or
14 (2) the 4 most recently completed calendar quarters immediately preceding
15 the start of the benefit year only if the individual applying for benefits does not qualify for
16 any benefits under § 8–802 of this title using the definition in item (1) of this subsection.
17 (c) “Base period employer” means an employing unit who paid wages to an
18 individual during the base period of the individual for covered employment.
19 (d) “Benefit year” means a 1–year period that begins:
20 (1) on the 1st day of the 1st week for which an individual first files a claim
21 for benefits; or
22 (2) if an individual already has had a benefit year, on the 1st day of the 1st
23 week for which the individual files a claim for benefits after the termination of the
24 preceding benefit year.
25 (e) “Benefits” means the money that is payable under this title to an individual
26 who is unemployed.
27 (f) “Board of Appeals” means the Board of Appeals of the Maryland Department
28 of Labor established under § 8–5A–01 of this title.
29 (g) “Calendar quarter” means the period of 3 consecutive calendar months ending
30 on March 31, June 30, September 30, or December 31, except as otherwise provided by the
31 Secretary by regulation.
32 (h) “Child support” means an obligation that is enforced under a plan that:

